name: Rumah Makan Sari Asih
address: Jalan Raya Denpasar - Gilimanuk Km. 77, Yeh Embang Kangin, Mendoyo, Yeh Embang Kangin, Kec. Mendoyo, Kabupaten Jembrana, Bali, Indonesia
review 1: Great place to rest after long trip. Plenty food choices. Have toilet and mushollah facility. Havingseveral chairs and lesehan. Next to SPBU. Plenty of parking spaces. Greatplace to rest while on trip from denpasar or gilimanuk.
review 2:
If you on traveling go to Denpasar but hungry in the halfway... I suggest to stop here, the taste like Javanese food in java.

Traditional menu... Especially the snack (dadar jagung & tahu petis) & soto daging are delicious.
This restaurant was huge enough, available parking lot, clean & bright.
review 3:
They served good food, I order opor ayam and nasi goreng Pete both are nice.
Restaurant clean, toilte clean, big parking space. They have lesehan area also.
It's located in Raya Gilimanuk - Denpasar, If you're from Gilimanuk after Negara.
Keep up the good work.
review 4: Fast service, wide dining and parking area. Food doesn't tasted that good, a little bit pricey. They don't put price on the menu, so I'm not sure how much exactly is the price. Employee also lied about their sold out menu (duck and grilled chicken). When we ask again, they didn't give proper explanation whether it's already been reserved or not, they just get angry and doesn't really care about us.
review 5: We ordered ayam kampung penyet and taste is delicious but the service from owner was kinda annoying. At first we ordered 5 pcs then order again 3 pcs. Ow wrote 9 pcs ayam kampung in the invoice instead 8 pcs, I asked politely about this but she did not want to hear and was mumbling and even accusing us we ate 9 pcs but just wanna pay 8 pcs, fortunately the lady staff still remember and told the lady boss that we ate only 8 pcs instead of 9 pcs and in the end the lady boss did not even say apologize. What a good attitude. Sorry I did not take picture of the meals
